9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 534, L.D. 848, “An Act Regarding the
10 Retired County and Municipal Law Enforcement Officers and Municipal Firefighters
11 Health Insurance Program”
12 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
13 following:
14 'Sec. 1. 5 MRSA §286-M, sub-§12, as enacted by PL 2005, c. 636, Pt. A, §3, is
15 amended to read:
16 12. Report. The division shall submit a report to the joint standing committee of the
17 Legislature having jurisdiction over insurance and financial services matters in the Second
18 Regular Session of the 124th Legislature, and biennially thereafter, on the status of the
19 program, program participation, including enrollment data, and the financing of the
20 program, including the status of the fund, expenditures from the fund, current and projected
21 premium costs to the program and to program enrollees and a projection of funding needs
22 for the next 5 years. The report must provide options, based on projections of future need,
23 for changing the method of funding any state-paid premium subsidy, if such a subsidy is
24 authorized by law, and employee contributions.
25 Sec. 2. Open enrollment of Retired County and Municipal Law
26 Enforcement Officers and Municipal Firefighters Health Insurance Program
27 for current employees. Notwithstanding the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 5, section
28 286-M, subsection 5, from October 1, 2025 to November 30, 2025, a county or municipal
29 law enforcement officer or a municipal firefighter who is employed in the position of a
30 county or municipal law enforcement officer or a municipal firefighter, who has held the
31 position for longer than 5 years and who previously elected not to enroll in the Retired
32 County and Municipal Law Enforcement Officers and Municipal Firefighters Health
33 Insurance Program established in Title 5, section 286-M, subsection 1 may elect to enroll
34 in the program. If the eligible person enrolls in the program 5 or more years following the
35 effective date of hire, the eligible person shall contribute to the fund 3% of the eligible
