8 SUMMARY
99 This amendment directs the Department of Administrative and Financial Services,
1100 Office of Employee Health and Wellness to include in its required biennial report to the
1111 joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over insurance and financial
1122 services matters program participation enrollment data specific to the Retired County and
1133 Municipal Law Enforcement Officers and Municipal Firefighters Health Insurance
1144 Program. The amendment also establishes a contribution rate for the open enrollment
1155 period of the program.
